HEADWORD: Pentarchy
<hw>Pen"tar*chy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>pentarchie</ets>. See <er>Penta-</er>, and <er>-archy</er>.]</ety>
<def>A government in the hands of five persons; five joint rulers.</def>
<au>P. Fletcher.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>pentarchy</xex> of the
senses.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>A. Brewer.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

